Reduction of Motor Friction

<number>

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

  • Motor Friction is about 40% of the total System Friction 

  • Reduction in friction w/ low core loss material 

    • 50cs290 has about 52% lower loss than 50cs600 

    • Motors with 50cs290 showed about 40~45% reduced friction at low speed 

    • No need for reducing lamination thickness

Measures to Reduce Motor Thermal
--PP 126

  • Thermal reducing options tested on PSA BMPV motor 

    • Varnished stator 

    • New plastic insulator (copper filled) 

    • Varnished stator with new insulator 

  • Additional Thermal reducing options 

    • Potting the bottom end turn to motor housing 

  • Thermal couple on top of winding at each phase and rotor
